The paper discusses a cooperative model-based reinforcement learning algorithm for multi-robot systems, which involves exploring the state space and generating effective policies. This falls under the domains of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also involves planning and coordination, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
